<tr id="L140"><td><a href="#L140">140</a></td><td>KIRK:  Mister Spock.</td></tr>

<tr><td></td><td>LOCATION--Sickbay</td></tr>
<tr id="L141"><td><a href="#L141">141</a></td><td>BELE:  Well, Lokai, it's a pleasure to see you again. This time I'm sure our joining will be of a more permanent nature. Captain, you are to be congratulated. Never before has Lokai been rendered so quiescent.</td></tr>

<tr id="L142"><td><a href="#L142">142</a></td><td>LOKAI:  I will not return to Cheron with him, to a land of murdering oppressors!</td></tr>

<tr id="L143"><td><a href="#L143">143</a></td><td>KIRK:  I told you where you were going. I allowed your fellow countryman here simply as a courtesy.</td></tr>

<tr id="L144"><td><a href="#L144">144</a></td><td>BELE:  And you see how this killer repays you, as he repays all his benefactors.</td></tr>

<tr id="L145"><td><a href="#L145">145</a></td><td>LOKAI:  Benefactors? He's a liar. He raided our homes, tore us from our families, herded us together like cattle and then sold us as slaves!</td></tr>

<tr id="L146"><td><a href="#L146">146</a></td><td>BELE:  They were savages, Captain. We took them into our hearts, our homes. We educated them.</td></tr>

<tr id="L147"><td><a href="#L147">147</a></td><td>LOKAI:  Yes, just education enough to serve the master race.</td></tr>

<tr id="L148"><td><a href="#L148">148</a></td><td>BELE:  You were the product of our love! And you repaid us with murder.</td></tr>

<tr id="L149"><td><a href="#L149">149</a></td><td>LOKAI:  Why should a slave show mercy to the enslaver?</td></tr>

<tr id="L150"><td><a href="#L150">150</a></td><td>BELE:  Slaves? That was changed thousands of years ago. You were freed.</td></tr>

<tr id="L151"><td><a href="#L151">151</a></td><td>LOKAI:  Freed? Were we free to be men? Free to be husbands and fathers? Free to live our lives in equality and dignity?</td></tr>

<tr id="L152"><td><a href="#L152">152</a></td><td>BELE:  Yes, you were free, if you knew how to use your freedom. You were free enough to slaughter and to burn all the things that had been built!</td></tr>

<tr id="L153"><td><a href="#L153">153</a></td><td>LOKAI:  I tried to break the chains of a hundred million people. My only crime is that I failed. To that I do plead guilty.</td></tr>

<tr id="L154"><td><a href="#L154">154</a></td><td>BELE:  There is an order in things. He asked for utopia in a day. It can't be done.</td></tr>

<tr id="L155"><td><a href="#L155">155</a></td><td>LOKAI:  Not in a day. And not in ten times ten thousand years by your thinking. To you, we are a loathsome breed who will never be ready. Genocide for my people is the plan for your utopia.</td></tr>

<tr id="L156"><td><a href="#L156">156</a></td><td>BELE:  You insane, you filthy little plotter of ruin. You vicious subverter of every decent thought. Oh, you're coming back to pay for your crimes!</td></tr>

<tr id="L157"><td><a href="#L157">157</a></td><td>LOKAI:  I know you and all those with whom you're plotting to take power permanently. When I return to Cheron, you will understand what power is. I will have armies of followers.</td></tr>

<tr id="L158"><td><a href="#L158">158</a></td><td>KIRK:  It's now very clear you know each other extremely well, gentlemen. The only service this ship can offer is to bring you together. It is not a battlefield.</td></tr>

